flowRoot.flowPara: From January 2009 to August 2012 I worked for NCH Software.
Immediately after completing my studies at the AIE, I was hired by NCH software.
I have worked for several companies as a software developer, both in Australia as
well as Germany. My knowledge and expertise is full-stack, covering backend systems to
user-interface design. I have a special interest in user-interaction.
From June 2016 to December 2018 I worked for KIWI.KI GmbH as a full-stack developer.
At KIWI I was responsible for a major overhaul of the KIWI Portal app, the primary
interface for business customers into KIWI.KI systems.
From September 2012 to December 2015 I worked for General Dynamics Mediaware.
I am currently learning German at Deutsche Akademie für Sprachen, where I have acheived
A2 level and am continuing with B1.
Hi, I'm Josh - a software developer living in Berlin (age 29). I'm originally from Canberra,
Australia. I moved to Berlin in 2015 shortly after having a fantastic holiday there.
I am a full-stack developer, with experience ranging from web development (Python,
NodeJS, Javascript, HTML, CSS etc), to lower-level languages like C++ and Go.
In my free time I like to go bouldering, sing karaoke, and play volleyball.
